# Achi - Memory Bank / Project Context

## Documentation Maintenance Rules

**When making code changes, update documentation if:**
1. Adding/removing/renaming files or packages → Update `Project Structure` section below and relevant `docs/*.md`
2. Adding new routes or changing navigation → Update `Navigation Structure` section and `docs/UI_STRUCTURE.md`
3. Changing domain models → Update `Key Domain Models` section and `docs/DATA_MODELS.md`
4. Adding/changing API endpoints → Update `API Integration` section and `docs/API_INTEGRATION.md`
5. Changing build config or dependencies → Update `Version Summary` and `docs/BUILD_CONFIGURATION.md`
6. Adding new features → Update `Current Feature Status` section and `docs/FEATURES.md`
7. Changing architecture patterns → Update `Architecture` section and `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`

**Documentation files:**
- `.cursorrules` - This memory bank (quick reference for AI)
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` - Detailed architecture patterns
- `docs/FEATURES.md` - Feature documentation
- `docs/DATA_MODELS.md` - Domain and UI models
- `docs/UI_STRUCTURE.md` - Navigation and UI patterns
